                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="notes">
                    
                        <note n="1" xml:id="note-t-1">
                            

<p>The fourth printing of <ref target="biblio.xml#lit_63"/><hi rend="italics"><rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_512">Andersen</rs>’s prentenboek zonder prenten: <ref target="biblio.xml#lit_63">Vertellingen van de maan</ref></hi>, translated by <rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_681">J.J.L. ten Kate</rs> and published in 1870 by A.W. Sijthoff in Leiden, states the price on the cover: ‘15 cents’ (Reeks Algemeene bibliotheek, no. 8). The first edition of the <hi rend="italics">Vertellingen van de maan</hi> (Tales of the moon) dates from 1862. The tales, subdivided in the translation into ten evenings, relate events on earth as observed by the moon.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="2" xml:id="note-t-2">
                            

<p>Regarding ‘the packages in question’, <ref target="let066.xml#l-16">see letter 66, l. 16</ref>.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="3" xml:id="note-t-3">
                            

<p>
  Ps. 4:7 (in <hi rend="italics">KJ</hi> Ps. 4:6) and rhy. ps. 4:3.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                            

                        
                    
